ğŸ“š PROJECT OVERVIEW
================================================================================
This AI model predicts whether a student will PASS or FAIL based on various
academic and behavioral factors. It's a classic BINARY CLASSIFICATION problem
where we train an algorithm to learn patterns from historical student data.

ğŸ¯ WHAT MAKES A GOOD PREDICTOR?
================================================================================
Our model will consider these factors:

1. ATTENDANCE RATE (%)
   - How many classes did the student attend?
   - Range: 0-100%
   - Impact: Higher attendance â†’ Better chances of passing

2. PREVIOUS GPA
   - Student's cumulative grade point average
   - Range: 0.0-4.0
   - Impact: Strong indicator of academic capability

3. STUDY HOURS PER WEEK
   - Hours spent studying outside class
   - Range: 0-70+ hours
   - Impact: More study typically = higher performance

4. ASSIGNMENT COMPLETION RATE (%)
   - Percentage of assignments submitted
   - Range: 0-100%
   - Impact: Responsible students complete assignments

5. MID-TERM SCORE (%)
   - Performance in mid-term exams
   - Range: 0-100%
   - Impact: Direct measure of subject understanding

6. PARTICIPATION SCORE (0-10)
   - Class participation and engagement
   - Range: 0-10
   - Impact: Active learners tend to perform better

7. PREVIOUS FAILURES
   - Number of times student failed courses
   - Range: 0 or more
   - Impact: Historical pattern matters

OUTPUT: 
   - PASS (1) or FAIL (0) - Binary Classification

âš™ï¸ THE AI APPROACH
================================================================================

STEP 1: DATA COLLECTION
---------
Gather historical data from 1000+ students including:
  - Their learning metrics (attendance, study hours, etc.)
  - Their final results (pass/fail)

Example data format:
